Package: macsR
Type: Package
Title: Facilitate analysis of MACS results.
Version: 1.0
Date: 2012-03-05
Author: Mark Cowley
Maintainer: Mark Cowley <m.cowley@garvan.org.au>
Description: MACS (model based analysis for ChIP-Seq) is a popular program for
    converting ChIP-Seq reads into peaks. If produces a number of output files
    in a directory, which to my mind can be improved a little. This package
    imports these results, can improve the result files, and can annotate peaks
    with their nearest TSS and CpG island.
License: GPL-2
LazyLoad: yes
Depends:
    R (>= 2.13.1),
    plyr,
    ChIPpeakAnno,
    AnnotationDbi,
    xlsx
Imports:
    ChIPpeakAnno,
    IRanges
Suggests:
    org.Hs.eg.db,
    org.Mm.eg.db,
    org.Rn.eg.db,
    gdata
Collate:
    'fix.macs.output.R'
    'import.macs.peak.file.R'
    'annotate.macs.output.R'
    'macsR-package.R'
    'CpG-data.R'
    'get.full.path.R'
    'is.dir.R'
    'is.matrix.like.R'
    'is.tsv.file.R'
    'is.xls.file.R'
    'mget.chain.R'
    'move.column.R'
    'rename.column.R'
    'write.delim.R'
    'writeLines.xls.R'
    'mget2.R'
    'na.rm.R'
    'annotatePeakInBatch.examples.R'
    'read.xls.R'
